WEBVTT

00:13.671 --> 00:17.049
<i>(cars in distance)</i>

00:18.717 --> 00:22.179
Brother William,
would you like to read today?

00:39.697 --> 00:41.782
O, God, our heavenly father,

00:41.866 --> 00:45.744
who has commanded us to love
one another as Thy children.

00:45.828 --> 00:47.288
<i>(man screams)</i>

00:50.166 --> 00:54.753
<i>I could've killed them all.
I could've killed you.</i>

00:54.837 --> 00:57.798
<i>In town, you're the law.
Out here, it's me.</i>

00:57.882 --> 01:00.134
<i>Don't push it.</i>

01:00.217 --> 01:03.721
<i>Don't push it or I'll give you a war
you won't believe.</i>

01:03.846 --> 01:08.225
<i>- (man gasps)
- Let it go.</i>

01:09.268 --> 01:11.729
<i>Let it go.</i>

01:13.189 --> 01:16.400
<i>(man) He's stuck there.
He can't go any place!</i>

01:16.483 --> 01:19.737
<i>(second man) If you don't
fly this thing, Ray,</i>

01:19.820 --> 01:22.531
<i>I swear to God, I'm gonna kill you.</i>

01:25.242 --> 01:27.912
<i>(gunshots)</i>

01:30.414 --> 01:32.875
<i>(man) Hold it steady, you sonofabitch!</i>

01:34.001 --> 01:39.632
<i>(man whoops) Get that man a cigar!</i>

02:11.372 --> 02:14.041
<i>- (man) Get in the car.
- (woman) Get in the car!</i>

04:40.729 --> 04:43.023
William. William, your lace.

04:47.945 --> 04:52.032
William, where did you find this?
This watch doesn't belong to you.

04:52.115 --> 04:54.076
Do you understand?

04:54.159 --> 04:57.913
Jess, stop it. You put it back
where you found it, William.

05:02.960 --> 05:05.212
<i>(clicks tongue)</i>

05:07.798 --> 05:10.008
<i>(woman) Voila. Montez-le. Comme ça.</i>

05:10.092 --> 05:13.095
Toute droite. Toute droite comme ca,
un petit peut plus.

05:13.220 --> 05:15.180
Tres bien. Bravo, c'est magnifique.

05:44.960 --> 05:46.753
<i>(pine cone clatters)</i>

05:48.338 --> 05:50.340
<i>(pine cone clatters)</i>

05:56.179 --> 06:00.183
<i>(man) I'm saying it might be
in your interest to listen,</i>

06:00.267 --> 06:05.772
and you'd do well to keep your wits
about you when I talk about scree.

06:06.565 --> 06:09.025
OK? So, show time.

06:09.151 --> 06:11.194
Er, thanks for your help.

06:12.195 --> 06:15.532
Erm, we're gonna be watching
a documentary now,

06:15.615 --> 06:18.618
and you're not allowed
to watch television, are you?

06:19.661 --> 06:23.707
Right, you got something
to be getting on with? OK, good.

06:23.790 --> 06:25.500
Right.

06:26.710 --> 06:31.298
<i>(man) That is expensive and not for you
to be messing around with, alright?</i>

06:41.099 --> 06:46.938
<i>(TV) Fire. When treated with care,
it can be mars greatest tool.</i>

06:47.063 --> 06:50.400
<i>But, if used incorrectly,</i>

06:50.484 --> 06:53.612
<i>it can be his most deadly foe.</i>

06:53.695 --> 06:56.490
<i>(screaming from TV)</i>

06:57.824 --> 06:59.951
<i>- (door bangs)
- (man) That's it!</i>

07:00.035 --> 07:02.412
<i>- (boy) What?
- (man) You know damn well what!</i>

07:02.496 --> 07:04.831
<i>(boy) I don't have a tennis ball!</i>

07:06.875 --> 07:10.462
<i>- (door bangs)
- (children cheer)</i>

07:16.176 --> 07:18.094
<i>(ball thuds)</i>

07:20.263 --> 07:23.391
<i>(ball thuds rhythmically)</i>

07:30.232 --> 07:32.108
<i>(thudding stops)</i>

07:41.451 --> 07:43.870
Go on. Fetch.

07:50.835 --> 07:53.922
<i>Nice drawings. (imitates explosion)</i>

07:54.923 --> 07:57.384
- Rarrr!
- My book!

07:58.385 --> 08:00.679
Oh, sorry. There you go.

08:00.762 --> 08:04.182
Don't you want it?
I thought you said you wanted it. Hmm?

08:04.266 --> 08:06.893
- I thought you said you wanted it!
- No!

08:12.649 --> 08:15.235
<i>(man) Morning, Janet.
A couple of miscreants</i>

08:15.318 --> 08:19.531
for the attention of "She Who Must Be".

08:21.574 --> 08:23.618
- Lee Can'ter, sit down.
- Yeah.

08:23.702 --> 08:26.204
- Sit down.
- Alright.

08:27.330 --> 08:30.250
He's got St Vitus' Dance, that one,
I tell you.

08:30.333 --> 08:32.544
<i>(man) OK, thank you.</i>

08:33.586 --> 08:35.839
What is your name?

08:41.928 --> 08:43.972
Will Proudfoot.

08:45.140 --> 08:46.683
Listen, mate,

08:46.766 --> 08:50.103
I don't mind taking the blame
for this if you like.

08:50.228 --> 08:55.650
But, er, if I do, you, er, might
have to give me something in return.

08:57.235 --> 09:00.739
Fair enough. I always fancied a watch.

09:00.822 --> 09:05.201
You probably don't mind getting a
letter sent home and being tortured.

09:06.828 --> 09:10.623
Didrt you know? About the torture?

09:11.332 --> 09:14.252
Oh, yeah. The last time she tortured me,

09:14.335 --> 09:18.548
I could barely stand up for a week.
Pain like you'd never believe.

09:18.631 --> 09:21.593
Doctor said they might
have to amputate it off.

09:21.676 --> 09:24.429
<i>(buzzer)</i>

09:24.512 --> 09:27.640
Well, can't keep the lady waiting,
can we?

09:29.434 --> 09:32.020
Let's just, er,
get this over and done with.

09:32.103 --> 09:34.147
<i>(buzzer)</i>

09:38.234 --> 09:41.571
- I'll pray for you, Lee Can'ter.
- Cheers.

09:45.950 --> 09:48.328
<i>(buzzer)</i>

09:49.954 --> 09:52.707
<i>(buzzer)</i>

09:57.962 --> 10:02.300
<i>(panting) Dear God, make sure Lee
Can'ter doesn't get... too badly hurt.</i>

10:02.383 --> 10:04.803
<i>(rumbling / cheering)</i>

10:10.225 --> 10:16.648
<i>- (band play upbeat tune)
- (woman) Now, voici Michelle Gina.</i>

10:16.773 --> 10:20.068
Sharon Davy, Michelle DuBois.

10:20.985 --> 10:23.071
<i>- (all cheer)
- Gail Graham?</i>

10:26.449 --> 10:28.743
Dit bonjour a Marie Planté.

10:34.832 --> 10:36.793
David Smart.

10:38.086 --> 10:40.463
Voici monsieur Lucas Dupont.

10:42.590 --> 10:45.426
- Duncan Miller?
- Yep.

10:45.510 --> 10:48.137
Voici Monsieur Didier Revol!

10:53.685 --> 10:55.979
<i>(all gasp)</i>

10:56.062 --> 10:58.982
<i>(music stops)</i>

11:25.174 --> 11:27.093
Bienvenue, Didier.

11:34.183 --> 11:36.728
<i>(band play upbeat tune)</i>

11:40.565 --> 11:43.651
<i>(groans)</i>

11:45.528 --> 11:48.865
<i>- Let me help you, Lee Can'ter.
- (groans)</i>

11:48.948 --> 11:53.202
God, that bitch was rough. She must
have loved that bloody goldfish.

11:53.286 --> 11:57.665
I'll be alright though, in a week.
Maybe two. I don't know.

11:59.417 --> 12:02.336
Can you... smell that?

12:02.420 --> 12:04.881
That stench is the smell

12:04.964 --> 12:07.633
- of Lee Can'ter.
- Up yours, Tina.

12:07.759 --> 12:09.010
- Scab.
- Slapper.

12:09.093 --> 12:10.720
- Scab.
- Er, slapper.

12:10.845 --> 12:14.348
- Scab.
- I blame the parents.

12:14.432 --> 12:17.143
Well, that's me, then.
I'd better be off.

12:17.226 --> 12:19.145
<i>(groans)</i>

12:20.188 --> 12:22.565
<i>No, don't worry, I'll be fine. (groans)</i>

12:22.648 --> 12:25.902
Time heals all wounds. Oh, God!

12:28.488 --> 12:30.490
<i>(Can'ter) Come on! Damn it!</i>

12:38.664 --> 12:42.168
Had to be the one with the bloody
trailer on the back, didn't it?

12:42.293 --> 12:45.630
- Where are you going?
- Oh, erm...

12:45.713 --> 12:49.383
the Head said I could have the
afternoon off after her torturing me.

12:49.467 --> 12:52.595
How can you cycle with your leg all bad?

12:57.975 --> 13:00.645
- Right here?
- Yeah, exactly.

13:03.105 --> 13:05.024
<i>(cow moos)</i>

13:27.588 --> 13:31.175
<i>- (Will) Is this where you live?
- (Can'ter) Yeah, this is my house.</i>

13:31.300 --> 13:36.097
Yeah. Of course it isn't, you idiot.
It's a short cut. Keep pedalling.

14:00.371 --> 14:02.456
<i>(brakes squeak)</i>

14:06.377 --> 14:10.172
Hey, boy, that video you're selling me,
it all wonky.

14:10.256 --> 14:12.425
I can't see nothing but fuzzy lights.

14:12.508 --> 14:15.845
I told you about that, Dora.
It's your tracking.

14:20.933 --> 14:22.977
Are you alright, Frank?

14:26.689 --> 14:29.483
<i>- That's Frank.
- (coins rattle)</i>

14:29.567 --> 14:31.569
<i>(Will) So, this is where you live?</i>

14:31.652 --> 14:35.614
<i>(Can'ter) Oh, no. This is the family
business. My home's through here.</i>

14:53.257 --> 14:55.551
So, this is your home?

14:55.634 --> 14:58.554
Yep, this is it. Home, sweet home.

15:08.606 --> 15:10.149
<i>(buzzing)</i>

15:19.784 --> 15:21.410
Hold that a sec.

15:28.042 --> 15:30.127
What are you doing?

15:38.469 --> 15:40.513
I know what we could do.

15:40.638 --> 15:44.100
If you don't tell me where they are
hiding, then I have no choice

15:44.183 --> 15:47.937
but to shoot you and your cat.
Do you have any last requests?

15:48.020 --> 15:49.563
I...

15:51.023 --> 15:54.735
Skill. Skills on toast.

15:58.906 --> 16:02.076
You know, I've been thinking.
The watch is nice, but, well,

16:02.159 --> 16:04.578
it only really covers me
getting tortured.

16:04.662 --> 16:07.206
I did have to, you know,
take the blame and lie.

16:07.289 --> 16:09.708
What do I get for all that?

16:09.792 --> 16:11.710
I don't have another watch.

16:11.794 --> 16:16.674
I don't mean another watch. I get to
choose how you pay me back, right?

16:16.757 --> 16:18.676
- Right.
- To properly pay me back,

16:18.759 --> 16:22.096
<i>you'll be the stuntman in the film
I'm making for Screen Test,</i>

16:22.221 --> 16:26.559
and you're not allowed to tell anyone
or I'll smash your face in. Alright?

16:26.642 --> 16:29.478
<i>- What's Screen Test?
- Exactly. Top secret.</i>

16:29.562 --> 16:32.690
<i>- (car approaches)
- Oh, shit. It's Lawrence.</i>

16:45.160 --> 16:46.954
- Get up there.
- What?

16:47.037 --> 16:50.749
Get up there! Go! Come on!

16:57.298 --> 16:59.842
<i>- Lawrence.
- You made them pirates of Rambo?</i>

16:59.967 --> 17:01.552
Yeah. I was just doing it.

17:01.635 --> 17:04.471
<i>Don't use my camera
for that Screen Test bollocks.</i>

17:05.263 --> 17:08.934
I wasrt! Honest!
Lawrence, get 'em off me!

17:10.435 --> 17:12.229
Get off!

17:13.439 --> 17:16.191
<i>- (Lawrence) Come on.
- (Can'ter) Get off! Ow!</i>

17:19.737 --> 17:21.739
More torture?

17:22.906 --> 17:25.367
Yeah. It's not my day.

17:35.919 --> 17:39.048
<i>(music plays)</i>

17:56.065 --> 17:58.901
Oh, yeah, stay there. I'll be back in a
minute.

17:59.026 --> 18:01.195
- Hello, mate.
- Ooh-ohh!

18:01.278 --> 18:03.906
- What is that all about?
- Ooh-ohh!

18:12.623 --> 18:15.042
Happy birthday, bro.

18:15.125 --> 18:16.960
You... Oi!

18:20.047 --> 18:22.257
You thought I'd forgot, didn't you?

18:22.341 --> 18:25.219
<i>("Close To Me" The Cure
plays on radio)</i>

18:36.522 --> 18:39.691
- These are very nice. Thanks, mate.
- Cheers, mate.

18:40.818 --> 18:43.112
<i>Don't push it.</i>

18:43.195 --> 18:46.532
<i>Don't push it or I'll give you a war
you won't believe.</i>

18:48.075 --> 18:51.078
<i>- (man gasps)
- Let it go.</i>

18:51.161 --> 18:54.289
<i>(gunshots / rotors whir)</i>

19:01.880 --> 19:06.051
<i>(man) You don't wanna accept the fact
that you're dealing with an expert</i>

19:06.135 --> 19:10.639
<i>in guerrilla warfare,
with a man who's the best with guns,</i>

19:10.722 --> 19:14.101
<i>with knives, with his bare hands,
a man who's been trained</i>

19:14.184 --> 19:17.563
<i>to ignore pain, ignore weather,</i>

19:17.646 --> 19:22.484
<i>to live off the land, to eat things
that would make a billy goat puke.</i>

19:22.609 --> 19:27.990
<i>In Vietnam, his job was to dispose
of enemy personnel. To kill. Period.</i>

19:28.073 --> 19:30.409
<i>Win by attrition.</i>

19:30.492 --> 19:32.452
<i>Well, Rambo was the best.</i>

19:33.412 --> 19:37.624
<i>Are you telling me 200 men against
your boy is a no-win situation?</i>

19:37.708 --> 19:40.335
<i>- You send that many, don't forget...
- What?</i>

19:40.419 --> 19:43.297
<i>A good supply of body bags.</i>

19:43.380 --> 19:46.258
200 men!

19:52.931 --> 19:55.225
He's gone.

19:59.021 --> 20:01.398
You can come down now.

20:04.818 --> 20:07.070
<i>Do you have any last requests?</i>

20:08.113 --> 20:10.115
<i>(china smashes)</i>

20:14.244 --> 20:17.581
Oi, stuntman, your face
was well funny on that one.

20:19.875 --> 20:22.669
<i>(pants)</i>

20:27.341 --> 20:29.801
<i>(yells)</i>

20:33.263 --> 20:35.432
<i>- (yells)
- (dog barks)</i>

20:36.475 --> 20:40.145
<i>- (imitates gunfire)
- (woman) Henry, come back here!</i>

20:41.313 --> 20:42.689
<i>(dog barks)</i>

21:16.056 --> 21:19.684
<i>(voice booms) Who are you?</i>

21:21.311 --> 21:24.356
Who are you?

21:24.439 --> 21:26.983
<i>(thunder)</i>

21:29.986 --> 21:32.989
<i>- I am the son of Rambo!
- (thunder)</i>

21:33.073 --> 21:36.034
What have you done with my Dad?

21:37.494 --> 21:39.037
No!

21:51.133 --> 21:53.343
<i>(yells)</i>

21:59.766 --> 22:03.520
<i>(deep voice) The sins you commit
are for the good of others.</i>

22:11.987 --> 22:14.781
Come on, Dad. We're going home.

22:14.865 --> 22:17.367
<i>(pants)</i>

22:57.949 --> 22:59.326
<i>(explosion)</i>

23:12.297 --> 23:14.799
<i>(TV) The wheel
is mars greatest invention,</i>

23:14.883 --> 23:17.302
<i>but it is the greatest
bringer of death.</i>

23:17.385 --> 23:19.888
<i>(tyres screech / crashing)</i>

23:24.684 --> 23:27.771
<i>- (door slams)
- (children cheer)</i>

23:36.863 --> 23:39.574
You told anyone
you were over at my house?

23:39.658 --> 23:42.994
I swear to God, if you tell anyone
I'm making this film,

23:43.078 --> 23:46.623
I'll smash your face in.
You still owe me, right?

23:46.706 --> 23:49.209
So be at my house at ten tomorrow.

23:50.293 --> 23:52.337
And don't be late.

23:56.007 --> 23:59.094
We've finished watching TV now.
You can come back in.

23:59.177 --> 24:02.889
<i>(teacher) You'll learn something
very much to your advantage.</i>

24:02.972 --> 24:05.684
Yes, I promise to astonish you

24:05.767 --> 24:09.187
with news of how a river can operate

24:09.270 --> 24:12.941
above the level of the flood plain, OK?

24:13.024 --> 24:16.736
And how do they do that?
How does a river operate

24:16.903 --> 24:21.825
above the level of the flood plain?
Is it because it's a bit arrogant,

24:21.991 --> 24:24.369
thinks it's a bit better
than the flood plain,

24:24.452 --> 24:28.164
or is it because of active deposition
of silt in times of flood?

24:28.248 --> 24:31.126
Arrogant river? Deposition of silt?

24:31.209 --> 24:34.379
It is actually the silt,
and I'm going to show you...

24:34.462 --> 24:38.341
Erm, the silt
goes into a sort of super silt.

24:42.720 --> 24:46.224
Bless, O Lord, this food to our use
and bless us to your service,

24:46.307 --> 24:50.311
make us mindful of the needs of others,
through Jesus Christ, Amen.

24:55.108 --> 24:57.902
<i>(mother) Jess! Jess!</i>

24:59.737 --> 25:02.866
Only you could lose something
strapped to your wrist.

25:02.949 --> 25:05.160
I should've taken it off you.

25:07.912 --> 25:10.999
Don't go in that shed again.
Do you understand?

25:12.167 --> 25:14.252
Do you understand?!

25:21.176 --> 25:24.846
I need you all up early
for the preaching tomorrow.

25:24.929 --> 25:27.182
- But I can't come.
- Of course you can.

25:27.265 --> 25:30.518
- No, see, there's this boy at school...
- There's lots of boys.

25:30.602 --> 25:34.814
No, I mean... This one was badly hurt,

25:34.898 --> 25:38.651
and I promised to help him
with his chores tomorrow.

25:47.619 --> 25:49.621
What happened to him?

25:49.704 --> 25:52.916
He... He had a terrible accident,

25:52.999 --> 25:55.919
and I promised I'd help him
with his chores tomorrow.

25:57.170 --> 25:58.963
That's...

26:00.048 --> 26:02.342
That's very kind of you.

26:04.427 --> 26:07.055
Look, I'm sorry for getting angry
all the time.

26:07.138 --> 26:10.850
It's... Anyway, you can go
and help this boy if you want.

26:12.852 --> 26:14.896
Thanks, Mummy.

26:16.439 --> 26:18.441
<i>(sizzling)</i>

26:18.524 --> 26:21.569
<i>("I Can't Wait" Nu Shooz
plays on radio)</i>

26:23.363 --> 26:25.365
Two minutes.

26:26.240 --> 26:28.368
<i>(doorbell)</i>

26:36.417 --> 26:40.588
Good morning, Lee Can'ter.
I'm here to help you!

26:40.672 --> 26:42.382
Jesus Christ!

26:42.507 --> 26:45.426
<i>(Lawrence) Oi! The bacors burning!</i>

26:49.722 --> 26:51.724
Get in that bush.

26:54.352 --> 26:56.813
<i>(Will whispers)
I'm waiting in the bush. Shhh!</i>

26:57.855 --> 27:01.734
- Who was it?
- Oh, some Bible-basher. Here.

27:04.529 --> 27:07.031
Want brown sauce on that or what?

27:10.493 --> 27:12.453
Oi! What about my tea?

27:14.288 --> 27:16.374
- Ready?
- Ready!

27:16.457 --> 27:19.335
Three, two, one, go!

27:20.837 --> 27:22.964
<i>(Will screams)</i>

27:23.047 --> 27:24.674
<i>(Will groans)</i>

27:24.757 --> 27:28.636
- You alright?
- I'm alright, Lee Can'ter!

27:28.720 --> 27:31.180
- Ready?
- Yep, ready!

27:31.347 --> 27:32.890
And action!

27:33.808 --> 27:36.185
<i>(Will yells)</i>

27:38.146 --> 27:41.566
<i>Cut! Cut! (laughs)</i>

27:50.199 --> 27:52.493
And cut. Great.

27:53.619 --> 27:56.330
- Ready?
- Yep, ready!

27:57.248 --> 28:00.751
Right. Action!

28:02.753 --> 28:04.881
<i>(screams)</i>

28:05.006 --> 28:09.051
<i>- (snapping)
- (Will) Ow! Uh! Ohh!</i>

28:11.804 --> 28:14.640
Great. Cut. You alright, Will?

28:16.184 --> 28:18.186
Will?

28:18.227 --> 28:20.229
You alright, buddy?

28:22.565 --> 28:26.068
<i>- (yells)
- What are you doing?</i>

28:27.320 --> 28:30.740
<i>(yells) I am the son of Rambo!</i>

28:30.823 --> 28:33.367
<i>(yells)</i>

28:35.286 --> 28:37.580
Hang on.
You wanna be the son of Rambo?

28:39.207 --> 28:42.084
<i>(wings flutter)</i>

28:42.168 --> 28:44.378
<i>(alarm)</i>

28:50.468 --> 28:52.678
- I have to go now.
- Come back tomorrow.

28:52.845 --> 28:56.224
- I ain't finished yet.
- OK. Bye, then.

28:58.309 --> 29:01.103
Oh, and I'm glad your legs
are feeling better.

29:03.064 --> 29:04.857
Nutcase.

29:15.076 --> 29:17.036
<i>- (clattering)
- (Will) Ow!</i>

29:23.709 --> 29:25.711
Oh.

29:25.795 --> 29:28.589
I don't know
if I've made enough for five.

29:28.673 --> 29:31.676
I could share mine with you,
if you like, Brother Joshua.

29:32.718 --> 29:36.389
Oh, no. Well, erm... that won't be...

29:36.472 --> 29:39.183
I'm not staying. I just...

29:40.559 --> 29:43.479
I'll see you in the morning
for prayer meeting.

29:48.442 --> 29:50.319
Yes!

30:04.125 --> 30:06.293
<i>(bird squawks)</i>

30:15.553 --> 30:17.179
<i>(owl hoots)</i>

30:19.557 --> 30:22.018
<i>(sawing)</i>

30:22.977 --> 30:25.187
<i>(dog barks)</i>

30:32.945 --> 30:35.072
<i>(knock at door)</i>

30:36.449 --> 30:39.535
- Ah. You all set?
- Mother had an accident in the night.

30:39.618 --> 30:41.537
- Ah. Oh, dear.
- Two minutes.

30:41.620 --> 30:43.497
Of course.

30:45.875 --> 30:49.587
<i>(Will) I tried to dress Grandma,
but Jess took over.</i>

30:49.670 --> 30:52.465
William... your shoes.

30:52.548 --> 30:56.218
You got something else to wear?
We're leaving for prayer meeting now.

30:56.302 --> 30:59.764
- Oh, William.
- Shall I take them to the menders'

30:59.847 --> 31:02.224
<i>- and meet you there?
- (thudding)</i>

31:02.308 --> 31:05.352
<i>(Jess) Mummy!
Grandma's lying on the floor!</i>

31:05.436 --> 31:08.230
<i>(sighs) Yes. Meet us there.
Sorry about this.</i>

31:08.314 --> 31:10.357
Not a problem.

31:12.401 --> 31:16.155
- Good morning, William.
- Good morning, Brother Joshua.

31:32.254 --> 31:35.382
Should be ready by three o'clock.

31:40.888 --> 31:42.598
<i>(Will) Thank you.</i>

31:43.516 --> 31:45.684
<i>(bell rings)</i>

32:26.100 --> 32:28.310
<i>(man) Keep it in a straight line, woman!</i>

32:28.394 --> 32:31.730
- This is why I won't let you drive!
- Jesus!

32:31.814 --> 32:34.400
<i>- I've got everything!
- (bottles clink)</i>

32:34.483 --> 32:37.111
Yeah, I can see that, you freak!

32:40.322 --> 32:43.158
<i>(buzzing)</i>

32:51.083 --> 32:52.918
<i>(electricity crackles)</i>

32:53.877 --> 32:55.879
- Wow!
- Thanks.

33:07.558 --> 33:09.518
I think that's everyone.

33:17.317 --> 33:19.820
I'm sure he'll wait for us here.

33:39.048 --> 33:43.052
<i>- (Can'ter) What's the dog thingy?
- (Will) That's the flying dog.</i>

33:43.135 --> 33:47.598
He guards the prison where
the scarecrow keeps my dad, Rambo.

33:47.681 --> 33:50.476
<i>(Can'ter) Right, and why have they
got him prisoner?</i>

33:50.559 --> 33:52.895
<i>(Will) He's an evil scarecrow.</i>

33:52.978 --> 33:55.439
<i>(Can'ter) And then you save him, yeah?</i>

33:55.522 --> 33:57.024
Yes!

34:00.402 --> 34:03.280
OK, we'll do your story,
but we're doing it my way.

34:03.405 --> 34:06.283
It doesn't mean I have to split
the prize with you, OK?

34:06.450 --> 34:10.704
<i>(Will) Yes, Colonel! Whoo-hoo!</i>

34:11.955 --> 34:14.123
Son of Rambo, Take One. Click.

34:16.001 --> 34:19.670
<i>(Can'ter) OK, ready and action!</i>

34:21.130 --> 34:23.592
I've come to save you, Rambo!

34:24.967 --> 34:29.097
We need to leave here right now
before the evil scarecrow finds us!

34:29.181 --> 34:33.351
Oh. What about my tea?

34:33.435 --> 34:37.022
Oh, son,
it's like a prison with them lot

34:37.105 --> 34:40.650
marching in and out every five minutes,
shouting at you,

34:40.734 --> 34:45.197
turning you over
while you're trying to sleep.

34:45.280 --> 34:50.494
"Eat your food," they say.
It's not fit for dogs.

34:52.329 --> 34:56.750
And the screams at night.
There's folk screaming in their beds.

34:56.833 --> 35:02.673
But I don't know if they're hurting
or just... afraid of something.

35:02.756 --> 35:05.884
I'm rescuing you, Father!
We're going to escape!

35:05.968 --> 35:08.554
I need to spend a penny first.

35:08.637 --> 35:12.391
Lord have mercy! What are you doing?
I'll kill you! Get out of here!

35:12.474 --> 35:16.436
They make you look so stupid! They
should be ashamed what they do to you.

35:16.520 --> 35:18.480
The boy's taking me home.

35:18.564 --> 35:22.276
The boys was just pretending.
You're not going nowhere, pops.

35:22.359 --> 35:24.528
You're staying in your room.

35:25.779 --> 35:27.739
Yes.

35:28.782 --> 35:31.493
<i>(sniffs) They're on our trails.</i>

35:31.576 --> 35:34.621
You'd better swing across the lake.
I'll get back up.

35:34.705 --> 35:36.623
Meet you in the prison in one hour.

35:36.707 --> 35:40.836
Don't worry, I'm trained to ignore pain
and live off the land.

35:40.919 --> 35:42.713
Just go!

35:45.757 --> 35:47.634
They're firing at us! Take cover!

35:47.718 --> 35:50.095
<i>(gunshots /
"Ride Of The Valkyries"plays)</i>

35:50.220 --> 35:52.097
OK!

36:02.566 --> 36:05.193
Yeah, keep swimming to the other side.

36:05.277 --> 36:07.237
I can't swim!

36:08.655 --> 36:10.907
What do you mean, you can't swim?

36:14.619 --> 36:16.580
Oh, shit!

37:00.457 --> 37:03.376
<i>(both pant / cough)</i>

37:11.468 --> 37:14.429
Thank you for coming to save me,
Colonel Trautman.

37:14.513 --> 37:17.641
<i>(both laugh)</i>

37:31.029 --> 37:32.781
Will?

37:32.864 --> 37:34.741
Will?

37:41.039 --> 37:42.082
<i>(alarm)</i>

37:43.542 --> 37:47.379
<i>(Will) I'll just have to say I got
lost or something. I don't know.</i>

37:49.548 --> 37:53.760
<i>If this film doesn't win Screen Test,
I'm gonna be a monkey's uncle.</i>

37:54.803 --> 37:57.472
Right, come on.
We're gonna be blood brothers now.

37:57.639 --> 38:00.725
- What's blood brothers?
- Come here.

38:15.782 --> 38:18.118
How long do we have to hold it
like this for?

38:18.201 --> 38:20.996
Until we hear that wood pigeon again.

38:25.667 --> 38:28.044
I gave your watch to my brother.

38:29.212 --> 38:32.882
Oh, so I won't ever get it back, then?

38:32.966 --> 38:35.176
No. He likes it.

38:35.302 --> 38:37.971
Wasrt mine anyway. It was my dad's.

38:38.054 --> 38:41.766
Is he pissed off with you?

38:41.850 --> 38:44.102
He's dead.

38:44.936 --> 38:47.105
Oh. Right.

38:47.188 --> 38:50.942
- How did he die?
- Mowing the lawn.

38:57.741 --> 39:00.869
It wasrt the mowing that did it,
you idiot.

39:00.952 --> 39:03.038
He had a thing called an aneurysm.

39:03.121 --> 39:06.124
A little vein in his head popped,
and that was that.

39:06.207 --> 39:08.460
He just, sort of, fell to the ground

39:08.543 --> 39:12.339
and the lawnmower kept going
and tipped up and... into the fence

39:12.422 --> 39:15.967
and made this really loud noise
as if it was hungry or something.

39:16.051 --> 39:19.846
It kept going "Rrrr,"
until they switched it off.

39:21.139 --> 39:25.852
- Jesus! I hope my veins don't pop.
- Me, too.

39:25.935 --> 39:28.730
My brother said you can kill someone
with one punch.

39:28.813 --> 39:31.358
Really?
Yeah. If you hit 'em right in the nose,

39:31.441 --> 39:34.319
their bone goes up through their brain
and kills 'em.

39:34.402 --> 39:36.821
Wow! Has he ever killed anyone
like that?

39:36.905 --> 39:40.909
No. He could if he wanted to, though.
He's pretty skill at everything.

39:40.992 --> 39:43.286
Do you like him?

39:43.411 --> 39:46.539
Well, yeah, course I do.
He's my brother, isn't he?

39:47.665 --> 39:49.626
What about your dad?

39:49.709 --> 39:52.545
My dad? No.
He pissed off before I was born.

39:52.712 --> 39:56.341
Then my mum met Colin, the bloke with
the big hair? He owns the care home,

39:56.424 --> 39:59.052
so we all live there.
It's alright, I suppose.

39:59.135 --> 40:02.639
But he lives in Spain, so my mum's
always over there with him.

40:02.764 --> 40:05.100
She gets tons of duty-free and stuff,

40:05.183 --> 40:08.353
which is kind of skill,
cos it's mostly just me and Lawrence.

40:08.436 --> 40:11.940
We get to do what we want, muck
about. There's no-one to tell us off.

40:12.065 --> 40:14.526
Seriously, though, parents...

40:14.609 --> 40:18.738
You're pretty much better off
without 'em. That's what I say.

40:22.325 --> 40:24.953
- Colonel Trautman.
- Yeah?

40:25.036 --> 40:28.581
Not including the bit
about losing my dad's watch,

40:28.665 --> 40:31.376
this has been my best day of all time.

40:31.459 --> 40:34.420
<i>(wood pigeon calls)</i>

40:36.589 --> 40:39.759
Oh! We've scabbed.

40:43.805 --> 40:48.476
<i>(both) O my God, I've come to say
thank you for your love today.</i>

40:48.560 --> 40:53.064
Thank you for my family
and all the friends you give to me.

40:53.147 --> 40:57.360
Guard me in the dark of night
and in the morning, send your light.

40:57.443 --> 40:59.320
Amen.

41:08.079 --> 41:09.831
He's been lying, Mary.

41:09.914 --> 41:12.584
He's confused.
He's trying to be a good Samaritan.

41:12.667 --> 41:15.336
You've had more than your share
of loss in life,

41:15.420 --> 41:18.381
and none of us wants to see you
lose your son to outsiders,

41:18.464 --> 41:20.633
but you must speak with him now.

41:20.717 --> 41:24.262
<i>(Joshua) Warn him.
Let him know that the path he is on</i>

41:24.387 --> 41:28.933
can lead only to misery,
not just for himself but for all of you.

41:29.976 --> 41:33.771
There's a group meeting tomorrow.
I thought it might do him good

41:33.855 --> 41:35.898
to come along, get him back on track.

41:35.982 --> 41:40.987
- Could you get him out of school?
- Of course. I'll make sure he's ready.

41:47.201 --> 41:49.912
Well... good night, Mary.

41:59.339 --> 42:03.760
And the Lord must greatly resent
the attempt to pursue a double life

42:03.843 --> 42:06.346
that goes hand in hand with the world

42:06.429 --> 42:10.642
and presuming to be fully brethren
at the same time.

42:10.725 --> 42:12.769
Hear, hear.

42:12.852 --> 42:18.066
God is faithful, who has called us
into the fellowship of his Son.

42:18.232 --> 42:21.944
It works out that way,
instead of being enticed.

42:22.028 --> 42:24.614
God doesn't entice anybody into evil.

42:24.697 --> 42:30.328
We're enticed, led astray,
by our own flesh,

42:30.411 --> 42:33.039
according to the scripture.

42:44.175 --> 42:46.469
<i>(brakes squeak)</i>

43:00.358 --> 43:02.360
Oi, you! Come back!

43:04.237 --> 43:06.489
<i>- Come on, then!
- (man) Oi, you! Come back!</i>

43:06.572 --> 43:07.949
See ya!

43:22.880 --> 43:28.511
My father won't send us to your school.
He said the pupils are a bad influence.

43:28.594 --> 43:31.222
Is it true, Brother William?

43:33.099 --> 43:35.184
I suppose so.

43:57.123 --> 43:59.166
What are you looking at?

44:03.546 --> 44:05.673
<i>(cow moos)</i>

44:05.756 --> 44:08.885
Well, you'll be wearing this stuff
one day, mate.

44:39.999 --> 44:42.877
<i>(explosions)</i>

44:59.477 --> 45:01.479
Thank you for taking him, Joshua.

45:01.562 --> 45:04.815
We all need a little guidance
from time to time.

45:04.899 --> 45:08.319
I'd hoped he might see me
as a kind of father figure.

45:10.112 --> 45:12.615
- You were hungry.
- Yes, very.

45:17.662 --> 45:19.914
Well, I'd better be going.

45:32.051 --> 45:34.845
- Good night, Mary.
- Good night. Good night.

45:56.534 --> 45:58.828
- What was he saying?
- Come with me.

46:00.037 --> 46:02.623
He thought you were great.
Really, he did.

46:02.706 --> 46:04.792
<i>- (sighs)
- Next!</i>

46:12.925 --> 46:15.094
Where have you been, eh?

46:15.177 --> 46:17.972
If you didn't wanna make this film,
you should've said,

46:18.055 --> 46:20.975
rather than leaving me on my own
covered in ketchup!

46:21.058 --> 46:23.686
We're blood brothers,
or have you not remembered?

46:23.769 --> 46:25.980
I had to go to a meeting!
It's our religion!

46:26.063 --> 46:30.985
- Oh, my itchy blue beard.
- They made me go and it was all day!

46:31.068 --> 46:34.572
- I'm not supposed to be your friend.
- What's wrong with me?

46:34.655 --> 46:37.616
- I'm Plymouth Brethren.
- What is that supposed to mean?

46:37.700 --> 46:40.119
- It's our religion.
- Bollocks, Will!

46:40.202 --> 46:42.538
It's true.
If they find out we're friends,

46:42.621 --> 46:45.916
I'll be in the worst trouble ever.

46:46.000 --> 46:48.169
I didn't forget, Lee Can'ter.

46:48.252 --> 46:52.006
They made me go.
I swear it, on my heart!

46:53.424 --> 46:57.344
I'm not allowed to make the film
with you any more. It's forbidden.

46:57.428 --> 47:00.222
Well, I didn't wanna make it with you,
anyway.

47:02.933 --> 47:07.438
You, er, left your alarm clock in my
locker. You'd better go and get it.

47:07.563 --> 47:09.315
OK.

47:22.369 --> 47:24.413
Son of Rambo,

47:24.496 --> 47:26.999
say, hello, to your new

47:27.082 --> 47:29.084
flying dog.

47:29.168 --> 47:31.295
- Did you make this?
- Yeah.

47:31.378 --> 47:33.088
You made my flying dog!

47:33.172 --> 47:35.674
We've got ten minutes before lessons.
Let's go.

47:36.884 --> 47:40.262
- It looks just like my drawings!
- Alright, are you ready?

47:40.346 --> 47:45.976
- Yep.
- OK. Three, two, one, go! Whoo-hoo!

47:50.397 --> 47:54.234
Thank you, Lee Can'ter! It looks real!

47:54.360 --> 47:56.654
Right, down, boy.

48:12.336 --> 48:14.046
Non.

48:14.880 --> 48:18.008
Thanks for coming.
Next, Lucy Rogers, monsieur.

48:24.139 --> 48:26.475
Wait. Wait here, ladies.

48:28.185 --> 48:31.063
- Do you want more Coke?
- Forget this.

48:31.146 --> 48:34.566
- Forget this?
- Oui, forget this.

48:34.650 --> 48:37.903
But there's lots more for you to
have a go on. I can get others.

48:38.070 --> 48:41.824
<i>St Mary's is just down the road,
and they're all Catholic. (groans)</i>

48:48.330 --> 48:53.252
He's bored. He's so bored.
I don't know what to do.

48:56.213 --> 49:00.342
That... looks just like a flying dog.

49:04.138 --> 49:06.557
Whoa! Whoa! Mind the trees!

49:12.354 --> 49:17.234
- I can't control it!
- You're going towards the building!

49:38.088 --> 49:40.174
- Hold on!
- I can't!

49:43.719 --> 49:45.721
<i>(screams)</i>

49:45.804 --> 49:48.599
<i>(siren wails)</i>

49:57.733 --> 50:02.321
Can'ter! Don't you dare move,
you bally boy!

50:04.489 --> 50:07.576
- Lee Can'ter!
- At least we got the shot.

50:07.701 --> 50:10.704
Alright, skills. Get my camera
and put it in your locker.

50:10.829 --> 50:14.625
Don't let anyone see you or you'll be
in deep shit. Catch up with you later.

50:14.791 --> 50:17.252
You'll get in trouble.
You'll be tortured again!

50:17.336 --> 50:19.254
Oh, don't worry. Just go.

50:19.338 --> 50:21.965
<i>(siren wails)</i>

50:23.050 --> 50:24.843
Can'ter!

50:28.472 --> 50:30.474
Where's my book?

50:30.557 --> 50:33.894
This is great. It's amazing.

50:33.977 --> 50:38.482
- Wow! He's gonna love it.
- Yeah. Yeah, I think he will.

50:40.233 --> 50:42.778
<i>(all boo)</i>

50:43.528 --> 50:47.282
- Lee Can'ter!
- Don't worry, it's a week's suspension.

50:49.076 --> 50:51.119
Get in the car!

50:52.287 --> 50:54.623
<i>(Lawrence) Shut up! Get in the car.</i>

50:54.706 --> 50:56.750
<i>(teacher) Pipe down!</i>

50:58.293 --> 51:01.880
<i>(teacher) Sam Taylor-Wood,
I'll get you inside!</i>

51:02.798 --> 51:06.134
<i>- Gonna miss your scabby little friend?
- (teacher) Inside now!</i>

51:07.177 --> 51:09.346
<i>(teacher) That means you!</i>

51:09.429 --> 51:12.349
<i>- ("Cars" by Gary Numan plays)
- What?</i>

51:12.432 --> 51:14.726
You said you were coming back
last week.

51:15.560 --> 51:17.854
What? What?!

51:18.021 --> 51:20.232
Look... Look, hold on a sec, Mum.

51:20.315 --> 51:22.401
- Oi, it's Mum.
- Skill! Say hello for me.

51:22.484 --> 51:24.611
He says hello. Hello back.

51:24.695 --> 51:27.364
Now everyone's said hello,
when are you coming back

51:27.447 --> 51:30.242
cos the place
is turning into a shit hole?

52:17.914 --> 52:20.709
<i>(opera music plays)</i>

52:35.182 --> 52:38.101
You live by the gun,

52:38.185 --> 52:40.312
you die by the gun.

52:44.608 --> 52:47.152
We are soldiers.

52:47.235 --> 52:49.613
We know only to fight.

53:00.790 --> 53:03.001
<i>(imitates gunshot)</i>

53:15.972 --> 53:18.391
<i>(groans)</i>

53:22.520 --> 53:26.942
<i>(groans) I see a big light in the sky.</i>

53:27.817 --> 53:29.611
Adieu.

53:43.792 --> 53:45.794
You make movie?

53:46.836 --> 53:49.589
To be star of movie is my dream,
my friend.

53:50.548 --> 53:52.717
You want to be in our film?

53:52.842 --> 53:54.803
Yeah. Yeah.

53:57.138 --> 53:59.933
My book.

54:04.229 --> 54:06.231
I will be star of your movie.

54:08.775 --> 54:12.362
Do you want...
Do you want some bubble gum?

54:30.964 --> 54:32.966
<i>(Didier) I'm French, non?</i>

54:43.101 --> 54:46.771
What you doing? Me ask you to clean
the window, not play with it!

54:46.855 --> 54:50.775
Put some elbow grease into it!
Listen, boy, clean my window!

54:50.859 --> 54:52.610
I want to see my face in the window!

54:57.198 --> 54:59.492
<i>- (groans)
- There you go, Mike.</i>

54:59.576 --> 55:01.453
Cheers, Keith.

55:01.536 --> 55:05.874
Still, we do get to spend a glorious
week without devil-child Can'ter.

55:05.957 --> 55:07.542
Yeah.

55:13.173 --> 55:15.508
<i>- (growls)
- (screams) Jesus Christ!</i>

55:15.592 --> 55:18.052
<i>- You stupid bastard!
- (all laugh)</i>

55:18.178 --> 55:21.055
<i>(laughs sarcastically) Laughs!</i>

55:21.139 --> 55:22.807
Walkies!

55:40.116 --> 55:42.619
<i>(yells)</i>

55:45.538 --> 55:46.789
<i>(roars)</i>

55:50.418 --> 55:51.920
<i>(yells)</i>

55:55.757 --> 55:58.218
<i>(roars)</i>

56:03.598 --> 56:07.018
- Who are you, sir?
- Zey call me ze Wolf.

56:08.394 --> 56:12.440
I know ze earth, I know ze sky...

56:14.234 --> 56:16.361
...and I know ze tree.

56:17.570 --> 56:21.533
I am Son Of Rambo.
I come in peace to you, Wolf.

56:21.616 --> 56:23.826
Salut, son of Rambo.

56:25.119 --> 56:27.330
I'm trying to find my dad.

56:29.249 --> 56:33.586
We go by there and by there,
and I help you to find your daddy man.

56:34.462 --> 56:37.882
Oh. Thanks ever so much. Let's go!

56:40.551 --> 56:42.553
And cut. That was great!

56:42.637 --> 56:45.181
<i>English fool! (yells)</i>

56:45.265 --> 56:47.642
<i>- (imitates gunfire)
- Cut!</i>

56:47.725 --> 56:49.894
Thanks.

56:50.019 --> 56:52.814
<i>(alarm clock rings)</i>

56:52.939 --> 56:57.151
- Where did you get that gun?
- Ze Wolf is bad, non?

56:57.235 --> 57:01.114
- It looks real.
- Hmm, yeah.

57:01.823 --> 57:04.033
Oh, and just so you know,

57:04.200 --> 57:07.203
- "cut" means stop.
- It's not a problem for me.

57:07.287 --> 57:09.664
<i>One last word to those of you out there.</i>

57:09.747 --> 57:13.042
<i>You can still enter for
the Young Filmmakers competition.</i>

57:13.126 --> 57:15.795
<i>You need to be under 17
next August 30th,</i>

57:15.878 --> 57:20.216
<i>but here's an address to write to.
Screen Test, BBC Television...</i>

57:36.649 --> 57:39.277
<i>("A View To A Kill"
by Duran Duran plays)</i>

57:39.360 --> 57:41.404
It's OK. He is with me.

57:46.409 --> 57:48.953
<i>Swing across the lake. I'll get backup.</i>

57:49.078 --> 57:51.122
<i>I'll meet you in one hour.</i>

58:08.014 --> 58:11.059
<i>(Can'ter) Die, Son of Rambo!</i>

58:11.142 --> 58:13.144
<i>(Can'ter) I'm back!</i>

58:13.853 --> 58:17.648
It's OK! He's only joking! He always
does that. Don't you, Lee Can'ter?

58:17.732 --> 58:19.192
Stop.

58:20.359 --> 58:23.654
Wait! Wait! They're going
to help us make the film!

58:24.697 --> 58:27.158
He's from France, and he's an actor.
Arert you?

58:27.241 --> 58:29.952
- Yeah.
- My nose. Is it bleeding?

